1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:18,000
Gozar/Gorz is a controlled local-first prototype release candidate for Android UX, local profile lifecycle, platform automation, evidence, and review.

2
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:36,000
The safety boundary is explicit: this is not a production VPN, not a public routing product, and not suitable for sensitive communication.

3
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:58,000
The four-phase roadmap closes with Phase 4: controlled release readiness across Android, platform assets, detection, reporting, and reviewer evidence.

4
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:22,000
The Android Home screen introduces the controlled demo state, offline mode, route safety, evidence, diagnostics, and safety pause.

5
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:45,000
The offline connect flow demonstrates local session lifecycle behavior without relying on public infrastructure.

6
00:01:45,000 --> 00:02:06,000
The confidence screen shows deterministic scoring and explainable local signals.

7
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:28,000
The route policy screen shows the applied local route, 10.77.0.0/24, and blocked unsafe routes.

8
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:52,000
Evidence Package V2 includes redaction summary, checksum, diagnostics, route policy, and safety status.

9
00:02:52,000 --> 00:03:15,000
Safety Pause blocks new sessions, records audit events, and appears in diagnostics and evidence.

10
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:45,000
Terraform and Kubernetes assets describe local lab infrastructure, ClusterIP services, overlays, and NetworkPolicy.

11
00:03:45,000 --> 00:04:12,000
Prometheus and Grafana assets provide controlled release observability views and alerts.

12
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:38,000
SIEM-style detection rules evaluate redacted sample events and generate a local detection report.

13
00:04:38,000 --> 00:05:02,000
The incident summary uses deterministic offline logic and does not call an external model by default.

14
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:28,000
GitHub Actions document CI, Android, emulator smoke, readiness, Terraform, Kubernetes, detection, and release candidate workflows.

15
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:55,000
The production readiness report marks the review package ready while production-ready for real use remains NO.

16
00:05:55,000 --> 00:06:18,000
The final position is a controlled prototype release candidate for demo, portfolio, research, and platform-security review.
